<br>
Greater Knowledge:<br>
<br>
    I think this could be one of the rudimentary skills general casters could use starting at 51. This skill lasts for about 2-3 minutes and it's reuse delay is about 1 to 2 hours. What this skill is for is to allow you to use a spell that is one level higher then the spell level you are on. <br>
    So lets say, you want to use your level 54 Voltaic Draught and you are 53. you use the skill, and the first time the skill is used scribing the spell into your book. Afterwards you can just use the skill to nuke one level above the level you currently are in. This could be a wizard only skill, but it could fit into the general casters domain.So if you want to use more then one spell higher then your level you have to take a little more time using your skill to scribe the spell(s) that you would like to use. And you need to make sure you make the time count with the higher nuke. This could really ease the 54 and 59 depression phase. Any thoughts? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umerco81.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merco81</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/9/01 2:00:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=620.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm...</span><hr size=1> 83 views, no replies, that either means that this idea is too stupid to comment on or it has no flaws to argue about.... oh well &gt;) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/10/01 6:33:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=620.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/concussion.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm...</span><hr size=1> You can't sribe spells that are higher level than you 